n character syndrome is philosophically dangerous","standfirstLong":"Why romanticising your own life is philosophically dubious, setting up toxic narratives and an inability to truly love","duration":0,"creditsShort":null,"commentsEnabled":false,"settings":{"badgeColor":null,"cardPlayIconColor":null,"alignX":"center","alignY":"center","backdropStrength":3},"tags":[],"authors":[{"id":"99850","name":"Anna Gotlib"}],"image":{"url":"https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/8234919c-c007-42fa-b83f-25aee8effa69/essay-gettyimages-566353099.jpg","alt":"Photo of a person wearing large sunglasses with outdoor scenery reflected, resting their fingers on their chin in a thoughtful pose.","height":1252,"width":2000},"primaryTopic":{"title":"Ethics","slug":"ethics"},"topics":[{"slug":"technology-the-self","title":"Technology and the self"},{"slug":"stories-literature","title":"Stories and literature"},{"slug":"ethics","title":"Ethics"}],"section":{"title":"Philosophy","slug":"philosophy"},"createdAt":"2024-08-20T09:57:49Z"}],"preview":false,"geolocation":"us"},"__N_SSG":true},"page":"/essays/[id]/[geolocation]","query":{"id":"the-life-changing-magic-of-japanese-clutter","geolocation":"us"},"buildId":"d8As-95gVr8haG1HEkmUo","isFallback":false,"isExperimentalCompile":false,"dynamicIds":[65117],"gsp":true,"scriptLoader":[]}</script></body></html>